-- allium: 3
-- specs/cuda-native-dispatch/cross_device_event_chain.allium
--
-- Status: PLACEHOLDER. Bound by PHASE_CUDA_NATIVE_DISPATCH.md
-- commits C4 (outer cudaStreamBeginCapture wrapping compute_splits)
-- and C7 (libmgpu port to captured subgraphs).
--
-- Scope: in the captured multi-device cudaGraph_t, every cross-
-- device data dependency is expressed via a cudaEventRecord on the
-- producer stream + cudaStreamWaitEvent on the consumer stream
-- BEFORE the consumer reads the produced data. No data flowing
-- across devices is read on the destination device before its
-- producer-side event has been recorded.
--
-- Why this spec exists: cross-device race surfaces dominated Phase
-- 46 (CLIP encoder) and the NP=8 LM determinism flake. The
-- structural fix in this phase is to embed cross-device sync nodes
-- INTO the captured cudaGraph_t via cudaEventRecord + cudaStreamWait
-- Event primitives. The CUDA driver enforces these as graph edges;
-- no host-side barrier is needed.
--
-- PD2 (PHASE_CUDA_NATIVE_DISPATCH.md §10) confirmed CUDA 13.2's
-- cudaStreamCaptureModeRelaxed permits cross-device event waits to
-- be captured into a single multi-device graph. This spec binds
-- that the dispatcher actually USES this capability everywhere a
-- cross-device dependency exists.
--
-- Includes:
--   - External entities for CUDA streams, events, graph nodes.
--   - Contract for ConsumerWaitsForProducer — every cudaStreamWait
--     Event in the captured graph has a corresponding earlier
--     cudaEventRecord on the producer stream.
--   - Contract for NoMissingEdges — if data tensor T is produced
--     on device A and read on device B, an event-chain edge
--     A.stream→T.event→B.stream exists in the captured graph.
--
-- CODE REFS:
--   ik_llama.cpp/ggml/src/ggml-cuda.cu:4382-4511   cpy_tensor_async (already does record+wait)
--   ik_llama.cpp/ggml/src/ggml-backend.cpp:2126    sched_eval (host-side dispatch entry, to be rewritten by C1)
--
-- TBD: fill content when C4 lands. The captured-graph topology is
-- the binding invariant; this spec checks the graph's structural
-- shape after capture.

allium 3

